    <h2 class="h2">Privacy Policy</h2>
    <div class="row">
        <hr />
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <p>In this privacy policy, the expressions "we", "us" and "our" are a reference to Michael Hill Wholesale Pty Ltd (an Australian company) and Michael Hill LLC (together Michael Hill Jewellers).</p>
            <p>At Michael Hill Jewellers we want your on-line and in-store experience to be enjoyable and we take care to respect your privacy when you visit our web sites and our stores. We do this gladly because we know that if you have a good experience with us, you will want to visit our web sites and our stores again... and maybe even tell your friends about us. </p>
            <p>This privacy policy applies to personal information collected by us. It includes information on how Michael Hill Jewellers collects, uses, discloses and keeps secure, individuals' Personal Information. It also covers how Michael Hill Jewellers makes the Personal Information it holds available for access to and correction by the individual.</p>
            <p>If you have any concerns about the manner in which your personal information has been collected, used or disclosed by us, we have put in place an effective mechanism and procedure for you to contact us so that we can attempt to resolve the issue. We can be e-mailed at <a class="custom-anchor" href="mailto:privacyofficer@michaelhill.com">privacyofficer@michaelhill.com</a> or write to us at Customer Service, 835 North Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611 and our privacy officer will then attempt to resolve the issue.</p>
            <p>Generally, we use the information we collect about you for two purposes: to facilitate your order and to create a better, more personalised experience for you. Our electronic commerce and privacy standards are derived from the world's best business practices and we abide by the following principles:</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>1. Online information</h4>
            <p>1.1 We endeavour to provide clear, complete and up-to-date information online about our business and the products and services we offer. This includes how to get in touch with us. This information helps you to make informed choices. </p>
            <p>1.2 We keep complete and accurate records of online contracts when you accept one of our offers. Our system also helps you to keep an accurate record so there is no confusion about the contract.</p>
            <p>1.3 If you have a problem with any of our goods or services that you receive from us, our Website provides further information about how to make a complaint, obtain redress or pursue dispute resolution. We can be e-mailed at <a class="custom-anchor" href="mailto:inquiry@michaelhill.com">inquiry@michaelhill.com</a> if there is a problem.</p>
            <p>1.4 This website may offer links to other websites. Those websites may also collect your personal information (including information generated through the use of cookies) when you visit them. We are not responsible for how such third parties collect, use or disclose your personal information, so it is important to familiarize yourself with their privacy policies before providing them with your personal information.</p>
            <p>1.5 If you engage in electronic commerce on this Website, please be aware that cross-border shipments are subject to opening and inspection by customs authorities. In order to facilitate customs clearance and comply with local laws, we may provide certain order, shipment and product information (such as titles) to our international carriers and such information may be communicated by the carriers to customs authorities. Customs authorities require the value of the item to be stated directly on the package.</p>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>2. What is Personal information?</h4>
            <p>Personal information (or personally identifiable information) includes information or opinions (including information or an opinion forming part of a database), whether true or not, and whether recorded in a material form or not, about an individual whose identity is apparent or can be reasonably ascertained, from the information or opinion. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>3. Collection of your personal information</h4>
            <p>3.1 We only collect personal information that is necessary for what we do. </p>
            <p>3.2 The type of information we may collect from you when you place an order online or in store can include (but is not limited to) the following:</p>
            <p>
                (a) your contact information, including your name, e-mail address, mailing address, phone number and driver's licence number;<br />
                (b) financial and billing information, including credit card number, expiration date, security code, purchasing history, bank account details, invoice details and credit history if you apply for or use our retail credit services;<br />
                (c) your date of birth;<br />
                (d) your insurance policies and details, if applicable;<br />
                (e) your participation in, or response to, our marketing and promotional activities, such as entering into a promotional contest;<br />
                (f) your purchases and/or use of the services we offer; or<br />
                (g) other employment or financial details obtained as a result of any application you may make for credit.
            </p>

            <p>This enables us to process your order and to notify you regarding its status (e.g., that it is on its way, or if we are temporarily out of stock, etc.).</p>
            <p>3.3 As much as possible, we will collect your information directly from you. If we collect details about you from someone else, we will, whenever reasonably possible, make sure you know we have done this and why.</p>
            <p>3.4 When you engage in certain activities on our web site or in-store, such as ordering jewellery, entering a contest or promotion, filling out a survey or sending us feedback, we may ask you to provide certain information. It is completely optional for you to engage in these activities.</p>
            <p>3.5 If you elect to engage in these activities, we may ask that you provide us personal information, such as your first and last name, mailing address, email address, telephone and facsimile numbers, and other personal information. </p>
            <p>3.6 Depending upon the activity, some of the information we ask you to provide is identified as mandatory and some as voluntary. If you do not provide the mandatory data with respect to a particular activity or any other information we require in order for us to provide our services to you, we may be unable to effectively provide our services to you or you may not be able to engage in that activity.</p>
            <p>3.7 If you use our Website, we may utilise "cookies" which enable us to monitor traffic patterns and to serve you more efficiently if you revisit the site. A cookie does not identify you personally but it does identify your computer. You can set your browser to notify you when you receive a cookie and this will provide you with an opportunity to either accept or reject it in each instance.</p>
            <p>3.8 We may gather your IP address as part of our business activities and to assist with the operational difficulties or support issues with our services. This information does not identify you personally.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>4. How we may use and disclose your information</h4>

            <p>4.1 We will only use or disclose your personal information for the purposes for which it was collected or as consented to and/or as set out below. </p>
            <p>4.2 You consent to us using and disclosing your personal information to facilitate a purpose in connection with:-</p>
            <p>
                (a) if required, the verification of your identity;<br />
                (b) the processing of orders (either by us or you), including to communicate with you concerning such orders;<br />
                (c) any application you may make for our retail credit services, including but not limited to processing the credit application, conducting credit verifications and administering your credit account;<br />
                (d) the administration and management of our or your services, including charging, billing, credit card authorisation and verification and collecting debts;<br />
                (e) the improvement of our or your products or services (including to contact you about those improvements and asking you to participate in surveys about the products and services);<br />
                (f) the maintenance and development of our services, products, business systems and infrastructure;<br />
                (g) marketing and promotional activities by us and our related bodies (including by direct mail, telemarketing, email, SMS and MMS messages);
                <br />
                (h) to provide customer service functions, including handling customer enquiries and complaints;<br />
                (i) to offer you updates, or other content or products and services that may be of interest to you;<br />
                (j) our compliance with applicable laws;
                <br />
                (k) the sale, and matters in connection with a potential sale, of our business or company to a third party; and<br />
                (l) any other matters reasonably necessary to function as a jewellery retailer.<br />
            </p>
            <p>4.3 We may also use or disclose your personal information and in doing so we are not required to seek your additional consent:- </p>
            <p>
                (a) when it is disclosed or used for a purpose related to the primary purpose of collection detailed above and you would reasonably expect your personal information to be used or disclosed for such a purpose;<br />
                (b) if we reasonably believe that the use or disclosure is necessary to lessen or prevent a serious or imminent threat to an individual's life, health or safety or to lessen or prevent a threat to public health or safety;<br />
                (c) if we have reason to suspect that unlawful activity has been, or is, engaged in; or<br />
                (d) if it is required or authorised by law.
            </p>
            <p>4.4 We may also disclose personal information where necessary for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal claims to investigate or prevent actual or suspected loss or harm to persons or property, or as otherwise required or permitted by law. </p>
            <p>4.5 In the event we propose to disclose such personal information other than for reasons in 4.1 and 4.2 above, we will first obtain your written consent prior to such disclosure or use.</p>
            <p>4.6 If you have received communications from us and you no longer wish to receive those sorts of communications, you should contact <a class="custom-anchor" href="mailto:privacyofficer@michaelhill.com">privacyofficer@michaelhill.com</a> or write to us at Customer Service, 835 North Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611 and we will ensure the relevant communication ceases.</p>
            <p>4.7 Any other use or disclosure we make of personal information will only be as required by law or by this privacy policy or otherwise with your consent.</p>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>5. The types of organisations to which we may disclose your personal information</h4>
            <p>5.1 We may disclose your personal information to organisations outside of Michael Hill Jewellers. Examples of organisations and/or parties that your personal information may be provided to include:</p>
            <p>
                (a) offshore service providers, if any;
                <br />
                (b) related entities and subsidiaries of Michael Hill Jewellers; and<br />
                (c) our contractors and agents, including but not limited to any third party providers who undertake our billing and/or credit services on our behalf and/or any third party providers who provide us with ecommerce platform services.
            </p>
            <p>5.2 Your personal information is disclosed to these organisations and/or parties only in relation to the services we provide to you or for a purpose permitted by this privacy policy. </p>
            <p>5.3 Michael Hill advertises with Google and other third party eCommerce Service Providers. These parties may show you our advertisements based on your previous visits to our website (this information is generated through the use of cookies). If you do not wish to see these advertisements you can opt-out by visiting the Google advertising opt-out page here: <a class="custom-anchor" href="http://www.google.com/privacy_ads.html" target="_blank">http://www.google.com/privacy_ads.html</a>, by visiting <a class="custom-anchor" href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices" target="_blank">http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices</a> or by adjusting or turning off your cookie settings.</p>
            <p>5.4 We take such steps as are reasonable to ensure that these organisations and/or parties are aware of the provisions of this privacy policy in relation to your personal information. For additional information on the way in which these organisations and/or parties treat your personal information, you should contact <a class="custom-anchor" href="mailto:privacyofficer@michaelhill.com">privacyofficer@michaelhill.com</a> or write to us at Customer Service, 835 North Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>6. Direct Marketing</h4>
            <p>6.1 If you have given us your consent, or if such disclosure is within your reasonable expectations given the transaction or communication you have had with us, we may use your personal information, including any email address you give to us, to provide you with information and to tell you about products and services (including third party products and services) which we consider may be of interest to you. We may also provide your details to other organisations (including our related companies) but only for specific marketing purposes. </p>
            <p>6.2 If at any time you do not wish to receive any further marketing information from us, you may ask us not to send you any further information about products and services and not to disclose your information to other organisations for that purpose. You may do this by using the "unsubscribe" facility included in the email. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>7. Cross Border Disclosure</h4>
            <p>7.1 Michael Hill Jewellers stores can now be found in numerous countries around the world. This growth has facilitated a change in the way in which we store our data (which will include your personal information), both in the United States of America and overseas. </p>
            <p>7.2 Any personal information provided to Michael Hill Jewellers may be transferred to, and stored at, a destination outside of the United States of America, including but not limited to the United Kingdom and Australia. Personal information may also be processed by staff or by other third parties operating outside America who work for us or for one of our suppliers, agents, partners or related companies. By submitting your personal information to Michael Hill Jewellers, you agree to this transfer, storing or processing of your personal information outside of America.</p>
            <p>7.3 Please note that countries outside of America do not always have the same protection obligations as America in relation to personal information. However, we will take steps to ensure that your information is used by third parties securely and in accordance with the terms of this privacy policy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>8. Data quality and security</h4>
            <p>8.1 In this age of internet shopping, we have learned that customers require peace of mind when it comes to the security of using the internet. We have taken steps to help ensure your credit card details and other personal information are safe by developing and using a secure server that has the most up-to-date encryption (decoding) methods. You will appreciate, however, that we cannot guarantee the security of all transmissions.</p>
            <p>8.2 We will take all reasonable steps to:</p>
            <p>
                (a) make sure that the personal information we collect, use or disclose is accurate, complete and up to date;<br />
                (b) protect your personal information from misuse, loss, unauthorised access, modification or disclosure both physically and through computer security methods; and<br />
                (c) destroy or permanently de-identify the information if it is no longer needed for its purpose of collection.
            </p>
            <p>
                8.3 However, the accuracy of personal information depends largely on the information you provide to us, so we recommend that you:
            </p>
            <p>
                (a) let us know if there are any errors in your personal information; and
                <br />
                (b) keep us up-to-date with changes to your personal information (such as your name or address). 
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>9. Privacy of Children on the Michael Hill Jewellers Website</h4>
            <p>9.1 The U.S. Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act imposes certain requirements on websites directed toward children under age 13 that collect information on those children or on websites that know they are collecting personal information from children under age 13. Michael Hill Jewellers does not collect personal information from any person under age 13 as children are not permitted to use our Website. </p>
            <p>9.2 Michael Hill Jewellers requests that children under age 13 not to submit any personal information to us through this Website. If Michael Hill Jewellers becomes aware that it has inadvertently gathered personal information from children under age 13, it will promptly erase such information from its records.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>10. Access to and correction of your information</h4>
            <p>10.1 You are entitled to have access to any personal information relating to you which you have previously supplied to us. You are entitled to edit or delete such information unless we are required by law to retain it or permitted to retain it in accordance with this privacy policy. However, we may keep track of past transactions for our accounting and audit requirements. Furthermore, it may be impossible to completely delete your information because some information may remain as backups.</p>
            <p>10.2 If you would like access, delete or correct any records of personal information we have about you or if you believe any information we have about you requires correction, please contact <a class="custom-anchor" href="mailto:privacyofficer@michaelhill.com">privacyofficer@michaelhill.com</a> or write to Customer Service, 835 North Michigan Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611. We reserve the right to charge a fee for searching for and providing access to your information.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>11. Governing law </h4>
            <p>This privacy policy is governed by the laws in force in Illinois, United States of America. You agree to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of that jurisdiction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h4>12. Consent </h4>
            <p>12.1 By using this website or making a purchase in-store you are agreeing to the terms of this privacy policy and our website terms and conditions (when applicable).</p>
            <p>12.2 We reserve the right to modify our privacy policy as our business needs require. We will post such changes on our website, after which, your continued use of the website or making a purchase in-store shall be deemed to be your agreement to the modified terms.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
